The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Adhunik Metaliks has acquired Orissa Manganese amp; Minerals Pvt Ltd as its 100 per cent subsidiary to give shape to its mining plans. The company is planning manganese ore and iron ore mining in the next three to six months. It did not disclose the financial details of the deal. The manganese and iron ores can be sold in the open market to various end users. 

 Citigroup Global Markets has consolidated its stake in pharmaceutical company Granules by acquiring over 3 lakh shares in open market transactions. On April 3, the fund house bought the additional 2.46 per cent for an undisclosed amount. Citigroup now holds over 5 .2 per cent or 6.54 lakh shares in Granules.

 UTI Bank has opened a branch at Contai. The bank has a network of 488 branches, 53 extension counters and 2,298 ATMs across the country.

 LG Electronics has launched a portable DivX DVD player with a built-in 7-inch swivelling LCD screen. The product, which also has built-in stereo speakers, comes for Rs 12,990.

